  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 30:8",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 30:8",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Be not stiff-necked, as your fathers were ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— A metaphorical expression, taken from refractory oxen, which will not go forward, but endeavour to withdraw their necks and shoulders from the yoke, and go backward. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But yield yourselves unto the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Give the hand ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to him, that is, submit yourselves to him, by obeying his command, and renew your covenant with him: both which things were wont to be done among men, by the ceremony of giving the hand; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and enter into his sanctuary — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Come to worship in his temple at Jerusalem; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "which he hath sanctified for ever — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hath hallowed, not for a transient and temporary use, but as long as the state and church of Israel shall have a being, whatsoever alterations may happen therein.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
