  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now be ye not stiffnecked, as your fathers were,.... Obstinate and refractory, like heifers unaccustomed to the yoke, which draw back from it, and will not submit to it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but yield yourselves unto the Lord; be subject unto him, or \"give the hand\" (q) to him, as a token of subjection and homage, or of entering into covenant with him, promising for the future to serve and obey him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and enter into his sanctuary, which he hath sanctified for ever; set apart for worship and service, until the Messiah should come: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and serve the Lord your God; there, in the temple, according to his prescribed will: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that the fierceness of his wrath may turn away from you; which had already broke out, in suffering the Assyrians to invade their land, and distress them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(q)  \"date manum\", Pagninus, Montanus, &c. ",
        "children": [
